@Node "Initial Release" "Update.guide/Initial Release"
@Next "Changes in 1.00"
@Prev "Main"
@Toc "Main"

Initial Release
***************

   @{b}*@{ub} Version 0.94b was the first release of FFRS.


@EndNode

@Node "Changes in 1.00" "Update.guide/Changes in 1.00"
@Next "Changes in 1.01"
@Prev "Initial Release"
@Toc "Main"

Changes in 1.00
***************

   @{b}*@{ub} FFRS now sends the report as a FTS-0001/39 compatible mail-packet
     (.PKT)

   @{b}*@{ub} new request report style

   @{b}*@{ub} you can have comments in the configuration file now...

   @{b}*@{ub} report now stored in T: instead of Mail:OutBound/

   @{b}*@{ub} no need to pass a datestamp from trapdoor any more

   @{b}*@{ub} FFRS now takes care of leading and trailing spaces in the
     requestfile (so you could request "myfile.lha !topsecret") (thanks
     to Dirk Spingler for this suggestion)

   @{b}*@{ub} Baudrate of 0 is changed to 2400 for TrapDoor's testfreq

   @{b}*@{ub} optimized directory scan and request treatment

   @{b}*@{ub} filenotes are sent with the request report now

   @{b}*@{ub} new option (NO)WILD to disable wildcard search

   @{b}*@{ub} new option (NO)FIRSTOCCURENCE to stop wildcard search at the first
     match

   @{b}*@{ub} textfiles HEADER/FOOTER/ERROR can be sent in the report...

   @{b}*@{ub} DEFAULTSEND <file> ALWAYS sends the given file as a free download
     (as suggested by Christian Buchner)

   @{b}*@{ub} DATAPATH specifies the directory where accounting data is stored.

   @{b}*@{ub} kludged in NOCOMMENTS for DLG Sysops

   @{b}*@{ub} FROM/TO/ANYTIME statements


@EndNode

@Node "Changes in 1.01" "Update.guide/Changes in 1.01"
@Next "Changes in 1.02"
@Prev "Changes in 1.00"
@Toc "Main"

Changes in 1.01
***************

   @{b}*@{ub} FIRSTOCCURENCE would not work when all requests were denied

   @{b}*@{ub} fixed a problem in getting the system time

   @{b}*@{ub} some CRs in the reportfile were killed accidentally


@EndNode

@Node "Changes in 1.02" "Update.guide/Changes in 1.02"
@Next "Changes in 1.10"
@Prev "Changes in 1.01"
@Toc "Main"

Changes in 1.02
***************

   @{b}*@{ub} Error handling was totally broken (machine would crash)

   @{b}*@{ub} EXCLUDE and NOWILD did not work properly

   @{b}*@{ub} there were mistakes in the docs

   @{b}*@{ub} fixed a bug that could,in certain rare cases, cause a crash on exit

   @{b}*@{ub} I had FFRS tested with mungwall and enforcer. No problems showed
     up.


@EndNode

@Node "Changes in 1.10" "Update.guide/Changes in 1.10"
@Next "Changes in 1.24"
@Prev "Changes in 1.02"
@Toc "Main"

Changes in 1.10
***************

   @{b}*@{ub} OS 2.04 now required, arp has been dropped

   @{b}*@{ub} finally fixed the bug with FIRSTOCURRENCE and rejected requests

   @{b}*@{ub} comments are now allowed in the requestfile (;) for comptiblity
     with some other obscure mailer. Why can't they all cling to the
     specs ???

   @{b}*@{ub} DLG support

   @{b}*@{ub} CNet support

   @{b}*@{ub} accounting data now stored in fidonet.extra via traplist.library
     (obsoletes DATAPATH statement)

   @{b}*@{ub} totally rewrote internal handling and storage of requests

   @{b}*@{ub} new fancy request reports :-)

   @{b}*@{ub} added multiline capabilities; only one ffrs-task is allowed run
     while the other(s) are delayed (queued) until the first one has
     finished

   @{b}*@{ub} A log window is possible now (LOG2)

   @{b}*@{ub} introduced wordwrapping, respects CRs already in the text

   @{b}*@{ub} introduced external calls with  % parameters (log, .rlo etc.)

   @{b}*@{ub} changed accounting data format -> less space, request limits count
     on a 24h period instead of a daily limit

   @{b}*@{ub} added NODELISTLIB keyword

   @{b}*@{ub} added INDEXONLY functionality

   @{b}*@{ub} FFRS now requires a keyfile to work completely (all functions)

   @{b}*@{ub} added NODELISTLIB parameter


@EndNode

@Node "Changes in 1.24" "Update.guide/Changes in 1.24"
@Next "Changes in 1.30"
@Prev "Changes in 1.10"
@Toc "Main"

Changes in 1.24
***************

   @{b}*@{ub} Asynchronous, font sensitive status window. See PUBSCREEN and
     CLOSEDELAY.

   @{b}*@{ub} Update requests now supported.

   @{b}*@{ub} User definable request reports w/percent commands/formatting.

   @{b}*@{ub} Magics with wildcards (newest match sent).

   @{b}*@{ub} A real manual...

   @{b}*@{ub} NOUNLISTEDNODES keyword (deny requests if node or point's boss is
     not listed in nodelist).

   @{b}*@{ub} Add files to be sent to existing *.HLO if present (files will not
     get lost when session is aborted). See (NO)EXISTINGFLOW and
     OUTBOUND.

   @{b}*@{ub} Own date-to-string conversion functions to avoid confusion when
     locale.library is being used.

   @{b}*@{ub} CNet 2.19+ support.

   @{b}*@{ub} 4D-BBS support.

   @{b}*@{ub} Download counters also for filenotes. See (NO)UPDATECOMMENTS.

   @{b}*@{ub} FROM/TO work across midnight.

   @{b}*@{ub} DOS3 MAGIC to pass parameters to any program.

   @{b}*@{ub} Re-added DEFAULTSEND.

   @{b}*@{ub} Report packets can be kept and have an informative filenote. See
     PKTPATH.

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed NOMATCH.


@EndNode

