@Node "1.3 Beta 1" "Update.guide/1.3 Beta 1"
@Next "1.3 Beta 2"
@Toc "Changes in 1.30"

Changes in 1.30 Beta 1
======================

     bug fixes:

   @{b}*@{ub} changed FFRS to respect exclamation marks in filenames.

   @{b}*@{ub} fixed rare, but hazardous bug in percent formatting routines.

   @{b}*@{ub} OUTBOUND paramter was not recognized (Chris Quonoey).

   @{b}*@{ub} fixed bug in config scanner: FFRS did probably ignore the last few
     statements. ARGH!

   @{b}*@{ub} tried to fix date routines. Also applies to DateDir and FFRSTAT. An
     old problem. Sorry, forgot to fix it in 1.24. Please report if it
     works now.

   @{b}*@{ub} fixed date string for built-in report (problems with locale).

   @{b}*@{ub} changed commandline parsing so the sysop name is optional as
     documented.

     changes:

   @{b}*@{ub} major internal cleanup saves about 2K of code.

   @{b}*@{ub} compiled with SAS-C 6.1

   @{b}*@{ub} DOS3 is gone, just use DOS1/DOS2 with the %Q parameter.

   @{b}*@{ub} EXCLUDE is now ONE AmigaDos pattern. You may have only one EXCLUDE
     statement in your config.

     Example: EXCLUDE #?.0

   @{b}*@{ub} added (NO)KEEPPACKETS option. Default: NOKEEPPACKETS. If set,
     TrapDoor will not delete the request report packets after sending.

   @{b}*@{ub} NOMATCH is now also ONE statement. Wildcards allowed. Use AmigaOS
     pattern matching for multiple files.

     ex.: NOMATCH (files.bbs|#?.key)

   @{b}*@{ub} the builtin report is two characters less wide.

   @{b}*@{ub} files that have NOT been sent are now displayed in FFRS_Status
     together with a reason (Robert Hofmann).

   @{b}*@{ub} added FREE option. Use in conjunction with MAGIC and DIRECTORY

     example: DIRECTORY FILES:Test PASSWORD blah FREE (Michael
     Hettenbach).

   @{b}*@{ub} re-enabled "multiple magics".

     example:

     MAGIC TEST FILE FILES:File1.lha

     MAGIC TEST FILE FILES:File2.lha

     would send both file1.lha and file2.lha)

   @{b}*@{ub} added GROUPS to config.

     Example:

     GROUP MAX 91:#?

     GROUP MYPOINTS 2:246/71.#?
     FORGROUP (MAX|MYPOINTS)
     MAGIC Files FILE REQUEST:FileList.txt
     ALLGROUPS

     You can set groups a) via the the GROUP startement (GROUP <Name>
     <Pattern>) and b) via the supplied "Groupie" utility. See
     "Groupie.doc" for details. Groups defined in the config are
     checked first.

   @{b}*@{ub} updated to work with 4DBBS 2.0 (Charlie Oskarsson).

   @{b}*@{ub} beta versions will only work with a keyfile.

   @{b}*@{ub} FFRS now checks for the right index format.

   @{b}*@{ub} added SetVBuf() calls at several places to speed up operation under
     V39


@EndNode

@Node "1.3 Beta 2" "Update.guide/1.3 Beta 2"
@Next "1.3 Beta 3"
@Prev "1.3 Beta 1"
@Toc "Changes in 1.30"

Changes in 1.30 Beta 2
======================

     Beta 2 (not released)

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed DLG and filenote support. (Marcus Kuba, Andreas Schildbach)
     Also changed FFRS to read only the .fd file. This has the positive
     side effect that FFRS now reads the long file comments.

   @{b}*@{ub} some flags changed, this is a complete list of commands dealing
     with file comments:

     4DBBS                   Activate 4DBBS support
     CNET                    Activate support for CNets
     CNET219                 Activate support for newer CNets
     DLG                     Activate DLG support
     FILENOTES               Send AmigaDOS filenotes as file comments
     UPDATEFILENOTES         Update download counter in filenotes

     No file comments are sent by default.  SENDCOMMENTS and
     UPDATECOMMENTS are gone for better clarity. (NO)COMMENTS is gone.

   @{b}*@{ub} changed max bytes calculation to respect the fact that most
     connections are v.42bis today. MaxBytes is now Baudrate/9 * 60 *
     MaxMins, resulting in 266cps at 2400, 1600 cps at 14400 and 1866
     cps at 16800.  This should be more realistic than baudrate/10.
     (Andreas Schildbach).

   @{b}*@{ub} - fixed MAGICs with wildcards. All files matching were sent
     (Alexander Abt).


@EndNode

@Node "1.3 Beta 3" "Update.guide/1.3 Beta 3"
@Next "1.3 Beta 4"
@Prev "1.3 Beta 2"
@Toc "Changes in 1.30"

Changes in 1.30 Beta 3
======================

   @{b}*@{ub} DOS magics without parameters/%Q did not work. Fixed.  (Maurizio
     Fabiani) Also saved 1500 bytes of code by using CurrentTime()
     instead of time().

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed bug: DIRECTORY inside FORNODE was not correctly treated.
     (Alex Goerig)

     [later note: This has NOT been fixed.].


@EndNode

@Node "1.3 Beta 4" "Update.guide/1.3 Beta 4"
@Next "1.3 Beta 5"
@Prev "1.3 Beta 3"
@Toc "Changes in 1.30"

Changes in 1.30 Beta 4
======================

   @{b}*@{ub} recompiled the whole package without the global optimizer.

   @{b}*@{ub} several bugs have been confirmed, but not yet fixed. See the file
     "bugs" in this archive.

   @{b}*@{ub} DLG support did create a file named like the comment of a failed
     request (e.g. "not found or password error") in the current
     directory.  Fixed. OOPS.


@EndNode

@Node "1.3 Beta 5" "Update.guide/1.3 Beta 5"
@Next "1.3 Gamma 1"
@Prev "1.3 Beta 4"
@Toc "Changes in 1.30"

Changes in 1.30 Beta 5
======================

   @{b}*@{ub} split up my linker library in more parts so less unused code is
     incuded in the ffrs executable. Also applies to the other
     utilities.

   @{b}*@{ub} found a uninitialized BOOL variable in MAGIC routines causing
     unpredictable results.

   @{b}*@{ub} fixed a bug in MAGIC routines that caused FFRS to send one file
     multiple times when multiple files should be send for one magic.
     This change also allows update requests for multiple magics: FFRS
     will check the date for each file individually.

   @{b}*@{ub} NOMATCH was not working due to a typo.

   @{b}*@{ub} cleaned up request report. All problems like files mentioned three
     times in the report should be gone now.

   @{b}*@{ub} fixed security hole in file search routines. I will not go into
     detail to prevent misuse.

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed problems with files without a .fd file (DLG support).

   @{b}*@{ub} Hard-coded date routines for localized systems (wb 2.1 and up).

   @{b}*@{ub} dropped support for CNet below 2.19

   @{b}*@{ub} added SUMMARY keyword (prints a summary of DIRECTORIES and MAGICS)

   @{b}*@{ub} added DLGAREAS keyword. Example: DLGAREAS file:area.bbs adds all
     file areas with the FREQ bit set to DIRECTORY list. This is equal
     to typing e.g.  DIRECTORY FILE:24/ in FFRS.cfg. If you want to set
     passwords etc., define the area as NOT for file request in DLG,
     and add it manually in FFRS.cfg.

     Note: this has not been tested.


@EndNode

