Changes in 1.30 Gamma 2
=======================

   @{b}*@{ub} fixed problem with these nasty 100 bytes files created in the
     current directory.

   @{b}*@{ub} fixed bug: IndexFind would lock up when called from FFRS.

   @{b}*@{ub} changed FFRS to allow a value of zero for MAXTIME and MAXFILES.


@EndNode

@Node "FFRS Status" "Update.guide/FFRS Status"
@Next "FFRI"
@Prev "1.3 Gamma 2"
@Toc "Changes in 1.30"

The FFRS Status Utility
=======================

     changes from 1.1 to 1.2 beta

   @{b}*@{ub} should have white menus under V39.

   @{b}*@{ub} configurable via tooltypes or commandline. You should remove @{b}
     PUBSCREEN AND CLOSEDELAY @{ub} from ffrs.cfg.

     Template :

     @{b} PS=PUBSCREEN/K,@{ub}        Default: default public screen
     @{b} CD=CLOSEDELAY/K/N,@{ub}     Default: 15 seconds
     @{b} FONT=FONTNAME/K,@{ub}       Default: default font on screen
     @{b} FS=FONTSIZE/K/N,@{ub}       Default: default size on screen
     @{b} WINX/K/N,@{ub}              Default: 0
     @{b} WINY/K/N,@{ub}              Default: 0
     @{b} WIDTH/K/N,@{ub}             Default: depends on font
     @{b} HEIGHT/K/N@{ub}             Default: depends on font

     The abbreviations can only be used from shell.

   @{b}*@{ub} Listview gadgets are now cleared at FFRS startup.


@EndNode

@Node "FFRI" "Update.guide/FFRI"
@Next "Utilities"
@Prev "FFRS Status"
@Toc "Changes in 1.30"

The FFRI Utility
================

     1.3 beta 1

   @{b}*@{ub} ffrs.dirs/ffrs.files are gone. You should delete 'em after running
     FFRI. RUN FFRI before you use the new FFRS!

   @{b}*@{ub} the new file index (ffrs.index) can be crunched via Xpk. New
     parameter CRUNCHMODE. See Xpk docs for details.

     beta 2

   @{b}*@{ub} DLGAREAS added.

     beta 3

   @{b}*@{ub} DLGAREAS fixed (hopefully). Still untested.

     gamma 1

   @{b}*@{ub} DLGAREAS fixed (hopefully). Now a little tested.

     gamma 2

   @{b}*@{ub} DLGAREAS works since g1.

   @{b}*@{ub} Cosmetical changes.


@EndNode

@Node "Utilities" "Update.guide/Utilities"
@Prev "FFRI"
@Toc "Changes in 1.30"

The others Utilities
====================

   @{b}*@{ub} wrote IndexFind utility. Will find and display any file(s) in index
     that are not password protected. Will return RETURN_WARN (5) if no
     file has been found.

   @{b}*@{ub} added NOFANCY switch to IndexFind. You'll get just the complete
     filename (including path) for each file found. Useful for scripts
     and online for BBSes.


@EndNode

