@Node "2.0" "Update.guide/2.0"
@Next "2.1"
@Toc "Changes in 2.xx"

Changes in 2.0
==============

   @{b}*@{ub} Since the last official release (1.24), lot of change in the
     concept of FFRS. FFRS is now a FREEWARE, and all we may say is
     'Thank's for all the previous job made by Martin Kuhne'.

   Starting this release, was introduced some changes:

   @{b}*@{ub} FFRS respond with your real name if it could find your name in the
     nodelist under your NODE definition.

   @{b}*@{ub} More better support for CNet 2.60+, FFRS use now the subboard data
     file to find where are the data subdirectory of a frequed file.

   @{b}*@{ub} Recompiled with last DLG support (DLG version 1.0) dating from
     5-Jun-93.

   @{b}*@{ub} Use of Amigaguide for the manual.

   @{b}*@{ub} no more need of any key.

     FFRS is now a FreeWare.

     Permission is granted to make and distribute verbatim copies of
     this manual and programs provided the copyright notice and this
     permission notice are preserved on all copies.


@EndNode

